<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-673-584  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 673 584.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  July 9 1990 v4 n26 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Army proposes SBIS use for defense open systems. (Sustaining BaseInformation Services)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Army is proposing that its own plans for a coreadministrative software system be used as the springboard for anopen-systems environment for the three services.andP;  If the proposalis carried out, the army will have preserved the $800 millionSustaining Base Information Services (SIBS) system from beingeliminated in a Pentagon ADP consolidation plan.andP;  In addition, theservice is setting up joint data processing installations with theNavy, proposing a reduced number of such operations by the ArmyMateriel Command.andP;  The report is recommending that funds for SBISbe reallocated to support establishment of 18 regional Departmentof Defense data processing installations and consolidations.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Open SystemsProposalBusiness PlanningReportsUnited States. ArmyUnited States. Department of Defense.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>